.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-qr_tool \- Encode text, URLs, Wi-Fi credentials, and vCards into QR codes — render to
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility qr_tool
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Encode text, URLs, Wi-Fi credentials, and vCards into QR codes — render to
.SH ENCODERS (TRIED IN ORDER)
.PP
.IP \(em 4
\fB\fCqrencode\fP\fP — recommended, tiny native binary.
.IP \(em 4
\fB\fCpython3\fP + \fCqrcode[pil]\fP\fP — pure-Python fallback.
.PP
.SH DECODERS (TRIED IN ORDER)
.PP
.IP \(em 4
\fB\fCzbarimg\fP\fP (from \fCzbar-tools\fP).
.IP \(em 4
\fB\fCpython3\fP + \fCpyzbar\fP + \fCPillow\fP\fP.
.PP
.SH INSTALL
.PP
Platform   |   Command
Debian / Ubuntu   |   \fCsudo apt install qrencode zbar-tools\fP
Fedora / RHEL     |   \fCsudo dnf install qrencode zbar\fP
macOS (Homebrew)  |   \fCbrew install qrencode zbar\fP
Termux            |   \fCpkg install qrencode zbar\fP
Fallback (any)    |   \fCpip install "qrcode[pil]" pyzbar pillow\fP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
qr encode  --text "https://example.com"
qr encode  --text "hello world" --out ./qr.png
qr encode  --wifi HomeNet --psk hunter2 --enc WPA
qr encode  --wifi Guest --enc nopass
qr encode  --vcard "Ada Lovelace" --email ada@example.com --phone 555-0100
qr decode  --image ./qr.png
qr decode  --image ./photo.jpg --json
.EE
.PP
.SS Options
.PP
Flag   |   Meaning   |   Default
\fC--text TXT\fP   |   Encode plain text or URL   |   —
\fC--wifi SSID\fP   |   Encode a Wi-Fi login   |   —
\fC--psk PASS\fP   |   Wi-Fi password   |   empty
\fC--enc WPA\  |  WEP\  |  nopass\fP   |   Wi-Fi authentication   |   \fCWPA\fP
\fC--hidden\fP   |   Mark SSID as hidden   |   off
\fC--vcard NAME\fP   |   Encode a minimal vCard 3.0   |   —
\fC--phone\fP, \fC--email\fP, \fC--org\fP, \fC--title\fP   |   Extra vCard fields   |   —
\fC--out FILE\fP   |   Write PNG to FILE   |   terminal
\fC--size SMALL\  |  LARGE\fP   |   Terminal render density   |   SMALL
\fC--level L\  |  M\  |  Q\  |  H\fP   |   Error correction   |   M
\fC--margin N\fP   |   Quiet-zone modules   |   2
\fC--json\fP   |   JSON output (decode)   |   off
\fC--no-color\fP   |   Disable ANSI colors   |   off
.PP
.SH WI-FI PAYLOAD FORMAT
.PP
The Wi-Fi payload follows the ZXing convention:
.PP
.EX
WIFI:T:<enc>;S:<ssid>;P:<pass>;H:<hidden>;;
.EE
.PP
Reserved characters (\fC\\fP, \fC;\fP, \fC,\fP, \fC:\fP, \fC"\fP) in SSID and PSK are escaped
automatically.
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP    |   Success
\fC1\fP    |   Invalid input / decode found no QR
\fC2\fP    |   No encoder / decoder installed
.PP
.SH TERMUX NOTES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fCqrencode\fP produces UTF-8 block glyphs that render cleanly in Termux.
.IP \(bu 4
ASCII fallback (\fC--size LARGE\fP) is picked automatically when \fCNO_UNICODE=1\fP.
.IP \(bu 4
\fCzbar\fP needs the camera off during decode; the tool reads image files only.
